(Fly away glum blue sea...)

18
00:01:03.400 --> 00:01:09.130
That's the signal to open the door to a new world

19
00:01:03.420 --> 00:01:09.150
Atarashii sekai he no tobira wo hiraku aizu

20
00:01:08.550 --> 00:01:13.070
(Fly away glum blue sky...)

21
00:01:13.050 --> 00:01:18.060
Swaying on the waves, reaching beyond despair

22
00:01:13.070 --> 00:01:18.080
Namima ni yureteru zetsubou wo nukete

23
00:01:18.060 --> 00:01:25.530
Aiming for the other side of the horizon

24
00:01:18.080 --> 00:01:25.550
Suiheisen no mukougawa mezashite

25
00:01:25.660 --> 00:01:31.330
I've just now begun to search, over the splashing waves

26
00:01:25.680 --> 00:01:31.350
Boku wa ima sagashi hajimeta mizushibuki agete

27
00:01:31.330 --> 00:01:34.510
For the everlasting world

28
00:01:31.350 --> 00:01:34.530
Hateshinaku tsudzuku sekai he

29
00:01:35.820 --> 00:01:40.990
Afuredasu jounetsu wo mune ni doko made mo yuku yo

30
00:01:35.950 --> 00:01:38.860
With this overflowing passion in my chest

31
00:01:38.860 --> 00:01:40.970
I will go anywhere

32
00:01:40.970 --> 00:01:47.560
Seeking the light yet unseen

33
00:01:40.990 --> 00:01:47.290
Mada minu HIKARI motome

34
00:01:49.760 --> 00:01:56.100
Vearth

35
00:01:56.760 --> 00:01:59.020
Thank you, God!

36
00:02:00.270 --> 00:02:02.350
I can't believe after all that trouble

37
00:02:02.350 --> 00:02:04.900
the sky island turned out
to be the City of Gold!

38
00:02:05.360 --> 00:02:11.360
This must be a reward for being
so well-behaved, right, God?

39
00:02:11.360 --> 00:02:15.320
Hey, I thought you were scared
of this island's god?!

40
00:02:16.240 --> 00:02:20.540
God? Oh, who cares about him?
Is he worth more than gold?

41
00:02:21.750 --> 00:02:25.250
But, you just said, "Thank you, God!"

42
00:02:25.250 --> 00:02:28.040
I don't think even she
knows what she's saying!

43
00:02:48.360 --> 00:02:49.860
How futile.

44
00:02:58.620 --> 00:03:00.580
Hey, what is this place?!

45
00:03:00.580 --> 00:03:04.330
I'll bet that this is where
we'll find the next ordeal.

46
00:03:04.330 --> 00:03:07.040
There'll be another priest soon.
Stay alert!

47
00:03:07.040 --> 00:03:08.290
Aw, man...

48
00:03:08.290 --> 00:03:11.380
I'm all ordealed out, dammit!

49
00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:13.170
What's it gonna be?!

50
00:03:13.170 --> 00:03:14.470
String?

51
00:03:14.470 --> 00:03:15.470
Iron?

52
00:03:15.470 --> 00:03:16.510
Swamp?!

53
00:03:16.510 --> 00:03:18.300
It looks like an ordinary meadow.

54
00:03:18.300 --> 00:03:21.810
It's not ordinary!
Open your eyes and look around!

55
00:03:21.810 --> 00:03:25.600
Those sticks all have skulls on them!

56
00:03:25.600 --> 00:03:27.400
Oh, you're right! What the heck?!

57
00:03:30.520 --> 00:03:31.650
Something's coming.

58
00:03:34.940 --> 00:03:37.280
Here they come!

59
00:03:49.420 --> 00:03:50.290
You dirtbags!

60
00:03:50.290 --> 00:03:52.380
Gum-Gum...

61
00:03:53.050 --> 00:03:54.710
Balloon!

62
00:03:59.510 --> 00:04:00.800
What was that?!

63
00:04:00.800 --> 00:04:02.140
A paramecia...!

64
00:04:02.140 --> 00:04:03.810
Wyper, should we engage?!

65
00:04:03.810 --> 00:04:05.220
No, don't bother!

66
00:04:05.680 --> 00:04:06.560
Wait, he's...!

67
00:04:07.390 --> 00:04:10.980
Hey, you! What're you doing?!
You want a piece of us?!

68
00:04:10.980 --> 00:04:12.570
You bastards!

69
00:04:15.650 --> 00:04:21.070
So you were the Blue Sea people
causing an uproar in Skypiea.

70
00:04:22.370 --> 00:04:23.740
Hey, Luffy,

71
00:04:23.740 --> 00:04:26.580
that guy's the masked guerrilla
we saw on the White Sea!

72
00:04:26.580 --> 00:04:29.080
What's wrong with you...? Huh?!

73
00:04:29.460 --> 00:04:30.880
He's running on the clouds!

74
00:04:32.460 --> 00:04:34.210
Hey, stop! What do you want?!

75
00:04:34.210 --> 00:04:35.170
Your deaths!

76
00:04:36.880 --> 00:04:39.630
Sky island scary, sky island scary...!

77
00:04:40.260 --> 00:04:43.600
If you don't want to die,
go back to the Blue Sea immediately!

78
00:04:44.220 --> 00:04:48.520
If you keep interfering on this island...

79
00:04:49.640 --> 00:04:52.440
we'll eliminate you along with Enel!

80
00:04:53.820 --> 00:04:56.320
They're trying to kill Enel?

81
00:04:56.320 --> 00:05:00.150
Does that mean the guerrillas
and God are on different sides?

82
00:05:00.150 --> 00:05:01.780
They're not priests?

83
00:05:01.780 --> 00:05:07.410
Then let's leave them alone
and get through here quickly, Luffy!

84
00:05:07.410 --> 00:05:08.910
What'd you say, you dirtbag?!

85
00:05:08.910 --> 00:05:11.870
C'mon! I'll kick your ass!

86
00:05:12.250 --> 00:05:14.840
Stop it! Please stop!

87
00:05:14.840 --> 00:05:18.210
I'm coming over there, so stay put!

88
00:05:18.210 --> 00:05:22.090
I'll pay you back
for earlier with interest!

89
00:05:25.600 --> 00:05:27.600
Well, I say "go back," but...

90
00:05:28.220 --> 00:05:33.230
whether or not you have the ability
to go back is another story.

91
00:05:37.820 --> 00:05:40.030
Who are those guys?

92
00:05:40.030 --> 00:05:46.700
Well, we learned that they're
enemies of God Enel and us as well.

93
00:05:46.700 --> 00:05:48.450
Dammit...!

94
00:05:48.450 --> 00:05:50.370
What's with this island?

95
00:05:50.370 --> 00:05:51.540
We're moving on.

96
00:06:06.930 --> 00:06:08.260
I'll cover you!

97
00:06:09.430 --> 00:06:11.480
Save our comrade!

98
00:06:13.140 --> 00:06:14.190
Now!

99
00:06:56.060 --> 00:06:59.440
We've come quite a ways,
haven't we, Sanji?

100
00:07:00.400 --> 00:07:02.440
Haven't we, Sanji?!

101
00:07:02.440 --> 00:07:06.450
Yeah, and that meadow earlier
turned out to be nothing.

102
00:07:06.450 --> 00:07:09.410
Maybe we'll make it to
the altar without incident.

103
00:07:09.910 --> 00:07:11.790
The sun will set soon.

104
00:07:13.080 --> 00:07:15.540
The clouds are obscuring the sunset.

105
00:07:15.540 --> 00:07:18.380
So they have twilight
on sky islands, too.

106
00:07:31.680 --> 00:07:33.560
Wyper! Kamakiri and I will fight here!

107
00:07:36.190 --> 00:07:37.600
Help them over there!

108
00:07:37.600 --> 00:07:38.480
Got it!

109
00:07:52.990 --> 00:07:54.870
Chopper!

110
00:07:54.870 --> 00:07:56.620
Where are you?!

111
00:07:57.460 --> 00:07:59.540
What happened, Chopper?!

112
00:07:59.540 --> 00:08:01.130
Say something!

113
00:08:01.130 --> 00:08:04.010
Hey, the Merry's mast is gone.

114
00:08:04.010 --> 00:08:06.260
What kind of changes did he make?

115
00:08:06.260 --> 00:08:10.090
Get your head out of your ass!
Clearly the ship was attacked!

116
00:08:10.090 --> 00:08:13.430
Chopper! I'm sorry we took so long!

117
00:08:13.430 --> 00:08:16.680
It's safe now to come out!
You're still there, aren't you?!

118
00:08:17.310 --> 00:08:21.020
Stop hiding and
say something, Chopper!

119
00:08:21.860 --> 00:08:23.980
Perhaps he was torn limb from limb.

120
00:08:23.980 --> 00:08:25.690
Stop saying scary things!

121
00:08:26.900 --> 00:08:29.160
Hey, Chopper! Are you there?!

122
00:08:29.160 --> 00:08:32.160
Did something happen?!
Say something!

123
00:08:34.490 --> 00:08:35.750
Noth...

124
00:08:37.790 --> 00:08:38.540
Noth...

125
00:08:40.250 --> 00:08:43.920
Nothing scary happened!

126
00:08:45.340 --> 00:08:50.010
Okay, okay... You're strong.
So tell us everything that happened.

127
00:08:55.180 --> 00:08:58.600
How much will this thing keep looping?!

128
00:09:00.730 --> 00:09:02.480
This is fun!

129
00:09:05.230 --> 00:09:07.280
We're soaking wet!

130
00:09:08.400 --> 00:09:09.280
Hey, look!

131
00:09:09.280 --> 00:09:10.530
We found it!

132
00:09:10.530 --> 00:09:12.030
The Going Merry!

133
00:09:12.030 --> 00:09:13.950
That's the altar!

134
00:09:17.330 --> 00:09:19.460
Nami my sweet! Robin my love!

135
00:09:19.460 --> 00:09:21.460
Sorry to keep you waiting!

136
00:09:21.960 --> 00:09:25.040
I overcame the Ordeal of Love
to make it here!

137
00:09:25.040 --> 00:09:27.630
Was that it? That was the ordeal?

138
00:09:27.630 --> 00:09:29.470
Were you guys scared?!

139
00:09:29.470 --> 00:09:33.760
Now that Captain Usopp
is here, you're safe and sound!

140
00:09:33.760 --> 00:09:37.390
Looks like they're okay, too.
What a relief.

141
00:09:45.020 --> 00:09:46.520
The mast...

142
00:09:46.520 --> 00:09:47.440
is gone...

143
00:09:48.110 --> 00:09:49.860
U-Um... Usopp...

144
00:09:49.860 --> 00:09:54.030
I'm sorry. I fought really hard, but...

145
00:09:54.700 --> 00:09:56.830
a lot of things got burned.

146
00:09:56.830 --> 00:09:59.160
You're wounded! Are you okay?!

147
00:09:59.160 --> 00:09:59.950
Huh?

148
00:10:01.040 --> 00:10:01.790
Yeah.

149
00:10:04.130 --> 00:10:07.250
What a scary guy,
using a spear that can burn things.

150
00:10:07.250 --> 00:10:10.260
I'm just glad you
weren't the one burned.

151
00:10:11.260 --> 00:10:13.880
We'll worry about the ship later.

152
00:10:16.180 --> 00:10:19.350
I will become a more dependable man!

153
00:10:19.930 --> 00:10:21.310
Hey, Chopper!

154
00:10:21.310 --> 00:10:24.020
How did you chase off that priest?

155
00:10:25.520 --> 00:10:27.150
I used the whistle.

156
00:10:27.150 --> 00:10:29.400
The Sky Knight came to rescue me.

157
00:10:30.110 --> 00:10:31.860
That weird old guy? Where is he?

158
00:10:42.290 --> 00:10:45.170
So he fought this hard,

159
00:10:45.170 --> 00:10:47.790
even though he gave us
the whistle for free.

160
00:10:48.670 --> 00:10:51.170
If it wasn't for the Sky Knight,

161
00:10:51.170 --> 00:10:53.300
both the ship and I would be goners.

162
00:10:53.300 --> 00:10:57.430
We have nothing but questions for him,
but we should wait until he wakes.

163
00:10:57.930 --> 00:10:59.810
Thanks to you, too.

164
00:11:04.060 --> 00:11:05.390
Luffy!

165
00:11:07.520 --> 00:11:10.900
Since the ship is damaged
and the sun's setting,

166
00:11:10.900 --> 00:11:13.360
we'll return to Angel Island tomorrow.

167
00:11:14.650 --> 00:11:18.240
For now, let's head to the forest
and camp at the lakeshore.

168
00:11:18.240 --> 00:11:19.370
Why?

169
00:11:19.370 --> 00:11:23.870
The ship will get destroyed
if we have to fight here, right?

170
00:11:23.870 --> 00:11:25.330
Use your head!

171
00:11:26.170 --> 00:11:30.040
Also, it's probably easier
to fight on the shore.

172
00:11:30.920 --> 00:11:33.920
Yay! Alright! Camping! Party time!

173
00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:32.840
Yay!

174
00:11:33.920 --> 00:11:34.800
What?!

175
00:11:34.800 --> 00:11:37.510
Hey, wait! We're in enemy territory!

176
00:11:37.510 --> 00:11:38.590
You wanna camp?!

177
00:11:47.270 --> 00:11:49.100
Alright!

178
00:11:49.100 --> 00:11:51.940
The priests can predict our attacks using mantra!

179
00:11:49.440 --> 00:11:53.230
Well, everyone,
thanks for your reports.

180
00:11:53.230 --> 00:11:57.200
We've learned a lot from
the intel you've gathered.

181
00:11:56.200 --> 00:12:01.120
The bird blows flames!
The spear burns you!

182
00:11:56.200 --> 00:12:00.410
The part of Jaya we thought had sunk
was actually in the sky!

183
00:11:57.200 --> 00:12:00.410
However, the biggest discovery...

184
00:12:00.410 --> 00:12:01.120
is this!

185
00:12:00.410 --> 00:12:00.490
The part of Jaya we thought had sunk
was actually in the sky!

186
00:12:00.490 --> 00:12:00.570
The part of Jaya we thought had sunk
was actually in the sky!

187
00:12:00.570 --> 00:12:00.620
The part of Jaya we thought had sunk
was actually in the sky!

188
00:12:00.620 --> 00:12:00.660
The part of Jaya we thought had sunk
was actually in the sky!

189
00:12:00.660 --> 00:12:00.700
The part of Jaya we thought had sunk
was actually in the sky!

190
00:12:00.700 --> 00:12:00.740
The part of Jaya we thought had sunk
was actually in the sky!

191
00:12:00.740 --> 00:12:00.780
The part of Jaya we thought had sunk
was actually in the sky!

192
00:12:00.780 --> 00:12:01.120
The part of Jaya we thought had sunk
was actually in the sky!

193
00:12:01.120 --> 00:12:06.870
The priests can predict our attacks using mantra!
The spear burns you!
The bird blows flames!
The part of Jaya we thought had sunk
was actually in the sky!
Believe it or not, the City of Gold
the Saruyama Alliance was looking for is here!

194
00:12:07.250 --> 00:12:08.870
Really?!

195
00:12:08.870 --> 00:12:10.580
I already said that, didn't I?!

196
00:12:11.090 --> 00:12:13.920
So, what is this mantra thing?

197
00:12:13.920 --> 00:12:15.210
I don't know.

198
00:12:15.210 --> 00:12:17.220
Maybe it's something like instinct?

199
00:12:17.220 --> 00:12:18.050
Instinct, huh?

200
00:12:18.800 --> 00:12:21.430
Hey, Chopper! Should I
grind it more than that?

201
00:12:21.430 --> 00:12:24.310
Yes. Make it easy to swallow.

202
00:12:24.310 --> 00:12:27.140
His digestive tract is a little damaged.

203
00:12:31.690 --> 00:12:32.820
City of Gold, huh?

204
00:12:32.820 --> 00:12:35.030
This is the adventure
I've been waiting for!

205
00:12:35.030 --> 00:12:36.240
I can't wait!

206
00:12:37.440 --> 00:12:39.780
That's the spirit!
This simplifies things!

207
00:12:39.780 --> 00:12:41.200
Hey, hey, Luffy.

208
00:12:39.780 --> 00:12:44.160
The priests can predict our attacks using mantra!

209
00:12:41.200 --> 00:12:44.160
Have you forgotten
the guerrilla's warning?

210
00:12:45.160 --> 00:12:46.540
The god's gonna get angry.

211
00:12:46.540 --> 00:12:47.540
He's scary!

212
00:12:49.290 --> 00:12:50.580
Sounds fun, doesn't it?

213
00:12:50.580 --> 00:12:55.920
Well, as pirates, we can't back off
when there's treasure close by, can we?

214
00:12:55.920 --> 00:12:57.800
We've got plenty of enemies, too.

215
00:12:57.800 --> 00:13:00.510
It's gonna be a fight for survival.

216
00:13:00.510 --> 00:13:01.890
How exciting!

217
00:13:02.260 --> 00:13:03.890
You guys...

218
00:13:05.060 --> 00:13:08.180
Shouldn't you be
a tiny bit afraid of that god?!

219
00:13:08.180 --> 00:13:10.730
I wash my hands of this.
You'll be punished, really!

220
00:13:19.610 --> 00:13:20.740
Alright!

221
00:13:20.740 --> 00:13:24.410
Let's go find that gold!

222
00:13:25.530 --> 00:13:27.540
Run, Kamakiri!

223
00:13:29.870 --> 00:13:31.790
I owe you one, Kamakiri...

224
00:13:34.420 --> 00:13:36.090
Kamakiri!

225
00:13:36.090 --> 00:13:37.170
Dammit!

226
00:13:42.300 --> 00:13:44.550
Wyper! Kamakiri's down!

227
00:13:45.220 --> 00:13:46.260
What?!

228
00:13:50.600 --> 00:13:52.480
Dammit!

229
00:13:52.480 --> 00:13:54.440
And we were so close!

230
00:13:55.690 --> 00:13:57.610
How do you figure that?

231
00:13:58.280 --> 00:14:01.990
Once night falls, we'll have
an even greater advantage.

232
00:14:10.580 --> 00:14:13.330
Assist the wounded!
We're pulling back for now!

233
00:14:13.330 --> 00:14:15.380
Meet back at the outer island!

234
00:14:18.710 --> 00:14:20.510
I won't let you escape!

235
00:14:20.510 --> 00:14:22.010
Wait, Ohm!

236
00:14:23.550 --> 00:14:24.720
What is it?

237
00:14:25.970 --> 00:14:28.220
God Enel wants to see us.

238
00:14:43.280 --> 00:14:45.240
Man, this is boring!

239
00:14:45.240 --> 00:14:47.530
Who told you to stare at it?!

240
00:14:48.370 --> 00:14:53.620
Your only job is to put the distilled
water that collects in the container

241
00:14:53.620 --> 00:14:57.250
into the canteens so that we'll have
drinking water for tomorrow!

242
00:14:59.460 --> 00:15:01.510
Still...

243
00:15:01.510 --> 00:15:03.590
Sanji! We got lots of things!

244
00:15:03.590 --> 00:15:05.930
Oh! Good work! What'd you find?

245
00:15:05.930 --> 00:15:08.680
Walnuts, aloe, bananas, and garlic!

246
00:15:08.680 --> 00:15:09.850
Plus rats and frogs.

247
00:15:09.850 --> 00:15:12.020
Great! Toss it in the stew!

248
00:15:12.020 --> 00:15:14.850
Hold it! There were some
weird ingredients just now!

249
00:15:15.690 --> 00:15:18.360
You're right!
How careless of me!

250
00:15:18.360 --> 00:15:19.900
No garlic?

251
00:15:19.900 --> 00:15:21.820
That's not the issue!

252
00:15:21.820 --> 00:15:23.320
What's wrong...

253
00:15:23.780 --> 00:15:25.030
Miss Navigator?

254
00:15:25.530 --> 00:15:27.030
Wow, Robin!

255
00:15:27.030 --> 00:15:29.660
What's that blue thing? A gem?!

256
00:15:29.660 --> 00:15:30.780
Pretty, isn't it?

257
00:15:30.780 --> 00:15:32.240
But no, it's not a gem.

258
00:15:32.240 --> 00:15:34.710
Oh, a salt crystal, huh?

259
00:15:34.710 --> 00:15:36.920
That's a great find, Robin!

260
00:15:36.920 --> 00:15:38.920
I found it on the lakeshore.

261
00:15:38.920 --> 00:15:40.880
I thought it would be useful to have.

262
00:15:40.880 --> 00:15:42.420
It sure would!

263
00:15:42.420 --> 00:15:45.380
Salt is vital to surviving
in the wilderness!

264
00:15:47.180 --> 00:15:49.890
I'll take half the garlic and aloe!

265
00:15:49.890 --> 00:15:53.890
I can use it to make burn medicine
and antiseptic for the Sky Knight!

266
00:15:53.890 --> 00:15:54.890
Yeah?

267
00:15:55.230 --> 00:15:57.310
What about the frogs?

268
00:15:55.980 --> 00:15:57.310
No frogs.

269
00:15:57.310 --> 00:15:58.600
Hey, Zoro!

270
00:15:59.310 --> 00:16:01.360
You're not doing anything. Help out.

271
00:16:03.940 --> 00:16:08.160
You know, my swords
aren't meant to be used like this.

272
00:16:08.160 --> 00:16:12.410
Quiet! Disobey the cook
and you'll go without dinner!

273
00:16:16.410 --> 00:16:18.370
Huh?! We're eating rocks, too?!

274
00:16:18.370 --> 00:16:19.630
Are they tasty?

275
00:16:19.630 --> 00:16:20.750
Get real.

276
00:16:20.750 --> 00:16:22.090
This is stone stew.

277
00:16:22.090 --> 00:16:25.090
The heat from the cooked 
stone boils the stew.

278
00:16:26.170 --> 00:16:28.010
Stew is great!

279
00:16:28.010 --> 00:16:30.800
You get all the ingredients' 
nutrition without any waste!

280
00:16:30.800 --> 00:16:32.220
I see!

281
00:16:32.220 --> 00:16:34.060
Ah! We're having st–

282
00:16:34.060 --> 00:16:35.680
Don't open it!

283
00:16:37.060 --> 00:16:39.810
Sanji! I'm hungry!

284
00:16:39.810 --> 00:16:41.650
It's not even cooked yet!

285
00:16:42.020 --> 00:16:45.900
Besides, didn't you just eat
an entire roasted sky shark?!

286
00:16:45.900 --> 00:16:46.860
Yeah...

287
00:16:46.860 --> 00:16:49.200
but that was just to tide me over.

288
00:16:49.740 --> 00:16:52.620
Really, what kind of
stomach does he have?

289
00:16:52.620 --> 00:16:54.240
How improvident...

290
00:16:58.120 --> 00:17:00.620
What're you doing, Usopp?
Dinner's almost ready.

291
00:17:00.620 --> 00:17:01.790
Yeah, I know.

292
00:17:02.290 --> 00:17:06.630
Just thought I'd start hauling
the wood for the ship's repairs...

293
00:17:07.380 --> 00:17:08.720
You gonna swim across?

294
00:17:08.720 --> 00:17:10.260
Huh? Yeah.

295
00:17:10.260 --> 00:17:12.550
There're big sharks in there.

296
00:17:17.520 --> 00:17:20.770
I can fix it tomorrow!
Let's get dinner, Zoro!

297
00:17:22.940 --> 00:17:24.570
Yeah, yeah...

298
00:17:28.320 --> 00:17:29.860
Alright! Finished!

299
00:17:29.860 --> 00:17:32.490
Ladies first. Got it?

300
00:17:32.490 --> 00:17:33.320
Yeah.

301
00:17:33.700 --> 00:17:35.950
Alright! Everyone in your seats!

302
00:17:35.950 --> 00:17:38.540
I'll come around and serve it,
so eat before it gets cold!

303
00:17:38.540 --> 00:17:39.910
Alright, guys!

304
00:17:39.910 --> 00:17:43.380
Let's begin our strategy meeting
to decide what to do tomorrow!

305
00:17:43.380 --> 00:17:45.380
Ooh! Looks great!

306
00:17:45.960 --> 00:17:47.420
Everyone ready?

307
00:17:47.420 --> 00:17:49.880
First, let's review
Noland's picture book!

308
00:17:49.880 --> 00:17:54.140
It was 400 years ago when Noland
first discovered the City of Gold.

309
00:17:54.140 --> 00:17:58.060
But when he returned
to Jaya years later,

310
00:17:58.060 --> 00:18:00.390
there wasn't a trace of the gold!

311
00:18:00.390 --> 00:18:03.020
This stew sure is good! Just like–

312
00:18:04.100 --> 00:18:06.020
Hey! Are you listening?!

313
00:18:06.020 --> 00:18:08.610
I'm sorry, Nami! But he was–

314
00:18:08.610 --> 00:18:11.700
These sky island lunch 
boxes are great, too!

315
00:18:13.200 --> 00:18:14.820
Like I was saying...!

316
00:18:14.820 --> 00:18:19.080
Basically, during those few years,
this island, which is part of Jaya,

317
00:18:19.080 --> 00:18:20.660
rose up into the sky!

318
00:18:21.460 --> 00:18:24.630
You mean it rode up
the Knock-Up Stream?!

319
00:18:24.630 --> 00:18:27.420
Yeah. That's the only
possibility I can think of.

320
00:18:27.420 --> 00:18:31.670
Cricket said the sea floor explodes
at different places each time.

321
00:18:31.670 --> 00:18:35.390
I could see an island flying
after an explosion like that!

322
00:18:36.220 --> 00:18:42.310
But it's hard to believe that the forest
on Jaya is the same as this one.

323
00:18:42.310 --> 00:18:46.810
That's probably due to the composition
of sea and island clouds.

324
00:18:47.440 --> 00:18:49.440
It seems the sky island environment

325
00:18:49.440 --> 00:18:52.570
allows flora and fauna
to develop unusually quickly.

326
00:18:52.570 --> 00:18:56.780
That also explains the civilization
that was swallowed up by this forest.

327
00:18:56.780 --> 00:19:02.200
The south birds that saved us
at the lake were enormous!

328
00:19:02.200 --> 00:19:05.120
Yeah, they probably got bigger 
over those 400 years.

329
00:19:05.120 --> 00:19:07.250
But it's strange...

330
00:19:07.250 --> 00:19:10.750
Why did those huge
south birds save you?

331
00:19:10.750 --> 00:19:13.380
Yeah, I'm not really sure.

332
00:19:13.380 --> 00:19:17.470
But they all called
the Sky Knight "God."

333
00:19:18.600 --> 00:19:22.470
God?! Does that mean
we should beat up this old man?!

334
00:19:22.470 --> 00:19:25.100
Of course not,
you stupid loudmouth!

335
00:19:25.100 --> 00:19:27.810
Alright, that's enough!
Sit down, loudmouth!

336
00:19:27.810 --> 00:19:28.770
Yeah! Sit down!

337
00:19:28.770 --> 00:19:30.230
Who's this loudmouth?!

338
00:19:30.230 --> 00:19:30.980
It's you!

339
00:19:30.980 --> 00:19:36.780
Anyway, remember what Noland's 
log said about the City of Gold?!

340
00:19:36.780 --> 00:19:38.660
I know! He saw gold!

341
00:19:38.660 --> 00:19:41.990
Obviously, you loud loudmouth!
Think before you speak!

342
00:19:41.990 --> 00:19:47.370
I recall there being a giant gold bell,
and that there were south birds.

343
00:19:48.000 --> 00:19:51.750
There was an incomprehensible line
on the last page of his log.

344
00:19:51.750 --> 00:19:54.920
Just before he died,
Noland wrote a passage

345
00:19:55.300 --> 00:19:57.720
that said he saw gold
in the skull's right eye.

346
00:19:57.720 --> 00:19:58.680
That's it!

347
00:19:59.260 --> 00:20:00.350
Look at this!

348
00:20:00.350 --> 00:20:05.680
I rescaled Robin's Jaya map
to match the old Skypiea map!

349
00:20:05.680 --> 00:20:07.310
It's just an approximation,

350
00:20:07.310 --> 00:20:11.610
but when you line up the locations
of the beach houses together...

351
00:20:12.770 --> 00:20:15.530
See! This is how Jaya
looked 400 years ago!

352
00:20:17.280 --> 00:20:19.160
Whoa! It's a skull!

353
00:20:19.160 --> 00:20:20.740
It looks like a skull!

354
00:20:22.160 --> 00:20:23.080
Well?

355
00:20:23.080 --> 00:20:24.040
Awesome!

356
00:20:24.040 --> 00:20:25.910
Way to go, Nami!

357
00:20:25.910 --> 00:20:27.540
We did it!

358
00:20:27.540 --> 00:20:28.670
Then...

359
00:20:28.670 --> 00:20:30.750
the skull's right eye...

360
00:20:32.250 --> 00:20:33.380
...is right here!

361
00:20:34.300 --> 00:20:38.130
Noland was referring to
the shape of the entire island.

362
00:20:38.130 --> 00:20:42.890
But only half of it is left now,
so nobody could solve the mystery!

363
00:20:43.390 --> 00:20:45.140
I see!

364
00:20:45.140 --> 00:20:47.230
So that's why.

365
00:20:47.230 --> 00:20:48.980
Interesting.

366
00:20:48.980 --> 00:20:50.350
Treasure!

367
00:20:50.350 --> 00:20:51.860
Treasure!

368
00:20:52.190 --> 00:20:55.230
So we just need
to go straight to this spot!

369
00:20:55.780 --> 00:20:57.650
We can't leave the ship, though,

370
00:20:57.650 --> 00:21:00.360
so let's split into
two teams tomorrow!

371
00:21:01.700 --> 00:21:03.200
No doubt about it!

372
00:21:03.200 --> 00:21:06.950
There's a vast treasure trove
of gold waiting for us here!

373
00:21:07.700 --> 00:21:10.460
Ahh, what a meal!

374
00:21:11.500 --> 00:21:12.750
We get gold tomorrow!

375
00:21:12.750 --> 00:21:14.130
That's right!

376
00:21:15.000 --> 00:21:16.960
Think it'll be sunny again tomorrow?

377
00:21:16.960 --> 00:21:18.670
Well, we are above the clouds...

378
00:21:19.170 --> 00:21:21.050
It's gotten pretty late.

379
00:21:21.050 --> 00:21:23.430
We need to put out
any unnecessary fires...

380
00:21:23.430 --> 00:21:25.180
lest we reveal our location.

381
00:21:26.890 --> 00:21:28.390
How foolish!

382
00:21:28.390 --> 00:21:29.770
Did you hear that, Usopp?

383
00:21:29.770 --> 00:21:32.810
She wants to put out the fire!

384
00:21:33.480 --> 00:21:34.770
It's not her fault.

385
00:21:35.520 --> 00:21:40.030
She's lived in darkness until now.

386
00:21:40.030 --> 00:21:41.110
She doesn't get it.

387
00:21:42.610 --> 00:21:44.240
What do you mean?

388
00:21:45.490 --> 00:21:48.910
You've always gotta have a campfire!

389
00:21:48.910 --> 00:21:51.710
The desire to have a campfire at night,

390
00:21:51.710 --> 00:21:54.880
even if you're about to die,
is what makes you human!

391
00:21:54.880 --> 00:21:57.460
You're the stupid ones!

392
00:21:57.460 --> 00:21:59.840
Will you cut the crap already?!

393
00:22:00.470 --> 00:22:04.090
You know how dangerous
this forest is!

394
00:22:04.090 --> 00:22:04.970
Do not!

395
00:22:04.970 --> 00:22:07.310
There are priests! There are guerrillas!

396
00:22:07.310 --> 00:22:11.520
And even without them,
forests at night are dangerous!

397
00:22:11.520 --> 00:22:14.400
There could be wild animals
or monsters out there!

398
00:22:14.400 --> 00:22:15.520
Monsters?!

399
00:22:15.520 --> 00:22:17.980
Sky island scary, sky island scary...

400
00:22:17.980 --> 00:22:19.230
Hey, Luffy!

401
00:22:20.110 --> 00:22:22.280
Is this wood pile good enough?

402
00:22:22.280 --> 00:22:24.700
You guys are serious
about this, too?!

403
00:22:25.700 --> 00:22:27.160
It's all right, Nami.

404
00:22:27.160 --> 00:22:30.120
Wild animals are
actually afraid of fires.

405
00:22:30.620 --> 00:22:32.250
Behind you, behind you!

406
00:22:32.250 --> 00:22:34.120
Something's already behind you!

407
00:22:41.590 --> 00:22:44.430
Hey! It's saying something!
Come here, Chopper!

408
00:22:49.180 --> 00:22:51.020
♪ We're more than just companions ♪

409
00:22:51.020 --> 00:22:54.980
Let's get this party started!
It's the gold-hunting eve festival!

410
00:22:51.020 --> 00:22:53.180
♪ Beyond what you would call friends ♪

411
00:22:53.180 --> 00:22:56.480
♪ We're each others own FAMILY! ♪

412
00:22:55.560 --> 00:22:57.560
♪ While we're all on the sea ♪

413
00:22:56.480 --> 00:22:58.690
♪ Not one of us are siblings ♪

414
00:22:58.690 --> 00:23:01.190
♪ We don't share any blood ♪

415
00:22:59.230 --> 00:23:01.190
What is this?! It's delicious!

416
00:23:01.190 --> 00:23:03.320
Did you guys make this juice?

417
00:23:01.570 --> 00:23:05.910
♪ But our crew is still FAMILY! ♪

418
00:23:03.320 --> 00:23:04.990
It's delicious! More, please!

419
00:23:11.290 --> 00:23:14.660
♪ Survey maps galore, ♪

420
00:23:14.660 --> 00:23:19.210
♪ The biggest maps you've ever laid your eyes on ♪

421
00:23:19.040 --> 00:23:20.750
What is this?! It's delicious!

422
00:23:19.210 --> 00:23:21.920
♪ It wouldn't matter anyway, ♪

423
00:23:20.750 --> 00:23:22.760
Let's get the treasure!

424
00:23:21.920 --> 00:23:24.670
♪ You'll never find family like this ♪

425
00:23:22.760 --> 00:23:24.670
– Gold!
– Gold!

426
00:23:24.670 --> 00:23:29.470
♪ Only outstanding slackers and misfits ♪

427
00:23:28.930 --> 00:23:31.930
They even tamed the cloud wolves.

428
00:23:29.470 --> 00:23:33.100
♪ Can come aboard our MOTHER SHIP ♪

429
00:23:33.100 --> 00:23:37.020
♪ Forsake all reason, then maybe ♪

430
00:23:33.480 --> 00:23:38.610
No one else would dare revel
so raucously in the land of Enel.

431
00:23:37.020 --> 00:23:41.150
♪ You can sail along with us ♪

432
00:23:38.610 --> 00:23:41.150
Oh, you're awake!
Should you be moving about?

433
00:23:41.150 --> 00:23:44.530
I apologize. I tried to help you
but ended up being a burden.

434
00:23:42.940 --> 00:23:46.530
♪ EVERYDAY ride out the storm ♪

435
00:23:44.530 --> 00:23:46.780
What do you mean? You helped a lot!

436
00:23:46.530 --> 00:23:50.280
♪ That's all we can ask for ♪

437
00:23:46.780 --> 00:23:51.030
Thanks! I hear you saved
Chopper and our ship.

438
00:23:50.280 --> 00:23:54.120
♪ We'll find the greatest treasure, it's our quest, ♪

439
00:23:51.030 --> 00:23:52.040
It was nothing...

440
00:23:52.040 --> 00:23:54.290
There's still some stew.
Would you like some?

441
00:23:54.120 --> 00:24:00.290
♪ with the aid of our MOTHER SHIP ♪

442
00:23:54.290 --> 00:23:57.670
Oh, no thank you.
I must decline at this time.

443
00:23:59.500 --> 00:24:03.000
Oh?! The weird old guy woke up!
Thanks for all your help!

444
00:24:01.420 --> 00:24:05.220
♪ The best people share a quirk, yeah ♪

445
00:24:03.000 --> 00:24:04.130
Let's dance!

446
00:24:04.130 --> 00:24:05.840
Let's dance, Sky Knight!

447
00:24:05.220 --> 00:24:11.470
♪ They can laugh like no one else can! ♪

448
00:24:05.840 --> 00:24:07.430
You're supposed to be a doctor!

449
00:24:09.090 --> 00:24:10.300
Whoa, old-timer!

450
00:24:10.300 --> 00:24:12.430
How is Conis? Is she all right?

451
00:24:12.430 --> 00:24:16.940
Yes. She and her father
are at my house. Fear not.

452
00:24:12.430 --> 00:24:14.560
♪ We're more than just companions ♪

453
00:24:14.560 --> 00:24:16.640
♪ Beyond what you would call friends ♪

454
00:24:16.640 --> 00:24:20.060
♪ We're each other's own FAMILY! ♪

455
00:24:16.940 --> 00:24:17.770
Really?!

456
00:24:17.770 --> 00:24:20.400
That's great! I was so worried!

457
00:24:18.900 --> 00:24:21.860
♪ While there's fun and we're free! ♪

458
00:24:20.060 --> 00:24:22.020
♪ Not one of us are siblings, ♪

459
00:24:20.400 --> 00:24:23.270
I'm glad they're both safe!

460
00:24:22.020 --> 00:24:25.030
♪ We don't share any blood ♪

461
00:24:23.270 --> 00:24:25.490
Alright! Let's all toss
Chopper into the air!

462
00:24:25.030 --> 00:24:29.320
♪ But our crew is still FAMILY! ♪

463
00:24:25.490 --> 00:24:26.570
What for?!

464
00:24:41.630 --> 00:24:44.710
I heard you talking earlier...

465
00:24:45.210 --> 00:24:48.340
I understand this island
was once called Jaya?

466
00:24:48.340 --> 00:24:49.340
Yes.

467
00:24:49.340 --> 00:24:53.430
I take it you don't know
why this place

468
00:24:53.430 --> 00:24:57.060
is now considered holy ground?

469
00:25:04.270 --> 00:25:07.190
These distractions
could cost us the battle!

470
00:25:07.190 --> 00:25:10.320
Are you trying
to get in our way, Raki?!

471
00:25:11.410 --> 00:25:15.330
I feel truly sorry for Kamakiri.

472
00:25:15.700 --> 00:25:17.040
We're up against priests!

473
00:25:17.040 --> 00:25:19.960
If we don't each give our all,
we'll never make it to God's Shr–

474
00:25:19.960 --> 00:25:22.630
I know apologizing won't fix anything!

475
00:25:22.630 --> 00:25:26.300
But give that back!
It's Aisa's treasure!

476
00:25:26.300 --> 00:25:30.760
I promised I would get vearth for her!

477
00:25:29.920 --> 00:25:30.760
Shut up!

478
00:25:30.760 --> 00:25:32.470
Forgive me! Don't throw it away!

479
00:25:35.810 --> 00:25:39.140
Kamakiri... Your wounds...

480
00:25:39.640 --> 00:25:41.600
I can still fight.

481
00:25:44.440 --> 00:25:48.110
You're right—this is our best chance
to take back Upper Yard.

482
00:25:51.950 --> 00:25:56.580
With Satori gone, we actually
held our own in today's battle.

483
00:25:56.580 --> 00:26:00.790
So let's attack again
tomorrow, Wyper.

484
00:26:08.130 --> 00:26:10.720
For you Blue Sea people,

485
00:26:10.720 --> 00:26:14.840
the ground here
must seem quite natural.

486
00:26:14.840 --> 00:26:16.180
Yeah, it does.

487
00:26:17.060 --> 00:26:19.020
I see.

488
00:26:19.720 --> 00:26:20.850
But this ground...

489
00:26:21.640 --> 00:26:24.690
is something that does not
normally exist in the sky.

490
00:26:25.020 --> 00:26:30.190
Island clouds can raise plant life,
but they cannot give birth to it.

491
00:26:30.190 --> 00:26:33.660
Neither greenery nor soil
is naturally found in the sky.

492
00:26:40.870 --> 00:26:44.540
We call this "vearth."

493
00:26:46.130 --> 00:26:52.090
To those who live in the sky,
it is our eternal hope given form.

494
00:26:54.590 --> 00:26:56.300
Once we defeat Enel,

495
00:26:56.300 --> 00:27:00.270
we won't be needing to revere
a single bag of vearth any longer.

496
00:27:01.270 --> 00:27:03.480
Right, Wyper?

497
00:27:07.860 --> 00:27:09.230
We're going back.

498
00:27:09.230 --> 00:27:12.440
To the 400-year-old
homeland of the Shandians!

499
00:27:13.150 --> 00:27:16.450
C'mon, Zoro! Just for a second...!

500
00:27:16.450 --> 00:27:18.450
I'm not goin' with you!

501
00:27:18.450 --> 00:27:20.240
You're such a whiner!

502
00:27:20.240 --> 00:27:22.330
If you're scared,
then wait till morning!

503
00:27:22.330 --> 00:27:25.330
I would if I could!

504
00:27:25.330 --> 00:27:28.170
Just go pee by yourself.

505
00:27:29.920 --> 00:27:32.710
You're so cold-hearted, Zoro!

506
00:27:51.320 --> 00:27:53.150
What's that sound?!

507
00:28:04.120 --> 00:28:07.210
There shouldn't be
anyone with the ship.

508
00:28:08.750 --> 00:28:11.290
It's hard to see through all this fog.

509
00:28:46.660 --> 00:28:48.920
What's his deal?

510
00:28:49.290 --> 00:28:52.540
He goes to take a piss,
then falls asleep out here.

511
00:28:52.540 --> 00:28:54.300
He's hopeless.

512
00:28:55.420 --> 00:28:58.590
G-Ghost... G-G-Ghost...

513
00:28:59.220 --> 00:29:01.180
Just wake up from your dream!

514
00:29:01.550 --> 00:29:04.140
G-G-Ghost!

515
00:29:05.100 --> 00:29:05.930
There's a...

516
00:29:06.470 --> 00:29:08.890
ghost...!

517
00:29:11.150 --> 00:29:12.810
We are...

518
00:29:16.360 --> 00:29:17.360
Hey.

519
00:29:19.030 --> 00:29:23.160
God's Shrine

520
00:29:23.570 --> 00:29:25.790
Must be hard to talk...

521
00:29:26.620 --> 00:29:29.000
while you're biting your lower lip.

522
00:29:33.080 --> 00:29:34.670
How careless of me.

523
00:29:36.380 --> 00:29:38.130
I'm telling you,

524
00:29:38.130 --> 00:29:43.930
almighty Enel summoned us
because you let Wyper escape!

525
00:29:48.140 --> 00:29:52.520
Don't start acting haughty just because
you beat old Gan Fall, Shura!

526
00:29:53.150 --> 00:29:54.810
Amusing!

527
00:29:59.860 --> 00:30:03.410
God, the priests have arrived.

528
00:30:03.410 --> 00:30:05.280
Open the door.

529
00:30:15.170 --> 00:30:16.630
Not again...

530
00:30:16.630 --> 00:30:19.710
What are you doing?!

531
00:30:20.590 --> 00:30:22.680
You're so hopeless...

532
00:30:22.680 --> 00:30:24.180
Quiet!

533
00:30:24.180 --> 00:30:27.470
It's only because
these guys drag me down

534
00:30:27.470 --> 00:30:29.930
that I can't unleash my full power!

535
00:30:29.930 --> 00:30:35.360
I would fare much better if you
let me handle the entire island alone!

536
00:30:35.360 --> 00:30:38.860
That's some mighty big talk there!

537
00:30:38.860 --> 00:30:44.110
I'll show you just how
worthless your "powers" are!

538
00:30:48.950 --> 00:30:51.250
On the sorrowful path of enlightenment...

539
00:30:51.750 --> 00:30:53.620
The Ordeal of Iron!

540
00:30:53.620 --> 00:30:57.170
Your worthless ordeal
is nothing but pathetic!

541
00:30:59.550 --> 00:31:02.590
My swamp is the supreme ordeal!

542
00:31:03.130 --> 00:31:04.800
Want to give it a try?

543
00:31:05.470 --> 00:31:08.850
Master Gedatsu.
That must be tiring.

544
00:31:08.850 --> 00:31:12.640
To cross your arms, you need to put
your hands under your elbows.

545
00:31:13.430 --> 00:31:14.270
How careless of me!

546
00:31:14.270 --> 00:31:17.270
Come now! That is enough!

547
00:31:17.270 --> 00:31:19.940
You are in God's presence!

548
00:31:17.310 --> 00:31:19.940
Yama
Skypiean Abbot

549
00:31:19.940 --> 00:31:21.110
Presence?

550
00:31:21.940 --> 00:31:25.110
I sure as hell don't see him!

551
00:31:26.610 --> 00:31:28.200
Got you!

552
00:31:44.970 --> 00:31:47.640
I am God.

553
00:31:47.640 --> 00:31:50.260
See, I'm right here.

554
00:31:47.680 --> 00:31:55.180
Skypiea's One and Only
God Enel

555
00:31:50.810 --> 00:31:53.220
You must continue your training.

556
00:31:53.220 --> 00:31:55.100
You're all too weak.

557
00:31:55.100 --> 00:31:58.600
Do you want to end up
like that pitiful Satori?

558
00:31:59.360 --> 00:32:01.070
What is this?!

559
00:32:01.520 --> 00:32:04.150
What a horrible prank!

560
00:32:04.150 --> 00:32:08.070
You called us here
just to tell us that?!

561
00:32:08.070 --> 00:32:10.490
I was bored.

562
00:32:11.830 --> 00:32:13.290
Have a seat.

563
00:32:13.950 --> 00:32:19.130
You don't seem to have taken much
notice of those Blue Sea people...

564
00:32:19.130 --> 00:32:20.290
Almighty Enel.

565
00:32:20.290 --> 00:32:21.920
If you're referring to Satori...

566
00:32:21.920 --> 00:32:24.590
...he was simply too inexperienced...

567
00:32:24.590 --> 00:32:27.130
...with his lousy
"Ordeal of Balls" and all.

568
00:32:28.130 --> 00:32:31.100
As I said, you're weak, Shura.

569
00:32:33.260 --> 00:32:35.810
Their goal...

570
00:32:35.810 --> 00:32:37.350
is gold.

571
00:32:37.730 --> 00:32:39.020
Gold...

572
00:32:39.350 --> 00:32:42.270
How do they know about that?

573
00:32:42.860 --> 00:32:46.570
This island was originally
part of the Blue Sea.

574
00:32:46.570 --> 00:32:50.160
It's no surprise that those
from the Blue Sea know of it.

575
00:32:52.870 --> 00:32:55.540
Naturally, they will make
their move tomorrow.

576
00:32:55.540 --> 00:32:58.250
And the Shandians will attack again.

577
00:32:58.250 --> 00:33:02.630
The rules are that each of you
run an area of Upper Yard,

578
00:33:02.630 --> 00:33:06.550
but you're not allowed to
interfere with one another.

579
00:33:06.550 --> 00:33:09.840
Tomorrow, I will let you
come and go as you please.

580
00:33:10.640 --> 00:33:13.470
You can set up your ordeals
wherever you like.

581
00:33:14.140 --> 00:33:17.600
You can also ignore the rules
and go as wild as you want.

582
00:33:19.100 --> 00:33:21.690
What brought this on so suddenly?

583
00:33:21.690 --> 00:33:27.280
Well you see, I've almost
completed the Maxim.

584
00:33:27.280 --> 00:33:33.660
So let's put an end to this island
and set forth for the world of dreams!

585
00:33:36.490 --> 00:33:38.960
See! It's just like I said!

586
00:33:38.960 --> 00:33:40.960
Someone was here!

587
00:33:40.960 --> 00:33:45.130
– The Going Merry's been repaired!
– The Going Merry's been repaired!

588
00:33:45.920 --> 00:33:47.710
I saw it!

589
00:33:48.380 --> 00:33:51.380
It wasn't a dream, after all!

590
00:33:53.800 --> 00:33:55.100
The mast...

591
00:33:55.100 --> 00:33:59.140
It was completely snapped off,
but now it's all fixed!

592
00:33:59.140 --> 00:34:02.480
I hate to say it, but...
this repair job sucks.

593
00:34:02.480 --> 00:34:04.440
There sure are nice people out there!

594
00:34:04.940 --> 00:34:09.820
But who'd fix our ship
in a place like this?

595
00:34:10.490 --> 00:34:15.280
The only people we've met
in Upper Yard have been enemies.

596
00:34:16.200 --> 00:34:20.250
But it's not in flight mode
anymore, Usopp.

597
00:34:20.250 --> 00:34:21.120
Right...

598
00:34:22.500 --> 00:34:25.670
Yeah. That's got me wondering...

599
00:34:29.630 --> 00:34:36.640
How did the person know what
the Merry originally looked like?

600
00:34:36.640 --> 00:34:41.060
How'd they know it didn't have
a crest or wings or a tail?

601
00:34:43.440 --> 00:34:45.560
How did they know?

602
00:34:50.990 --> 00:34:55.240
Tell me, Merry. Who was that?

603
00:35:00.040 --> 00:35:02.330
Now, then. Here's the map.

604
00:35:02.330 --> 00:35:06.040
The search team will follow
this route, due south.

605
00:35:06.540 --> 00:35:09.750
The right eye should
hold some sort of ruins,

606
00:35:09.750 --> 00:35:13.050
so watch out for enemies
and bring back that gold!

607
00:35:13.050 --> 00:35:14.880
You make it sound so simple.

608
00:35:14.880 --> 00:35:18.890
Huh? You keep talking about the gold,
but you're not coming?

609
00:35:18.890 --> 00:35:21.180
No way! It's scary!

610
00:35:21.180 --> 00:35:24.310
You want the gold,
but without any danger!

611
00:35:24.310 --> 00:35:26.350
You're so weird, Nami! Weirdo!

612
00:35:26.350 --> 00:35:30.320
Meanwhile, we'll leave
the island on the Merry.

613
00:35:30.320 --> 00:35:32.070
We'll be in danger, too, you know.

614
00:35:32.400 --> 00:35:35.450
We'll head for the beach ruins
as fast as possible.

615
00:35:35.450 --> 00:35:37.320
Let's meet up there,

616
00:35:37.320 --> 00:35:39.780
and then escape from this sky island!

617
00:35:40.580 --> 00:35:43.830
We'll be filthy-rich pirates!

618
00:35:43.830 --> 00:35:45.370
We can buy whatever we want!

619
00:35:45.370 --> 00:35:46.540
Hooray!

620
00:35:46.540 --> 00:35:48.580
I can eat all the meat I want!

621
00:35:48.580 --> 00:35:51.920
Escape, huh? Sounds good to me!

622
00:35:52.590 --> 00:35:55.090
Look! The weather is so nice!

623
00:35:55.090 --> 00:35:56.590
We are above the clouds.

624
00:35:56.590 --> 00:35:59.390
Okay! Let's get to 
the eastern shore in one piece!

625
00:35:59.390 --> 00:36:00.350
Alright!

626
00:36:00.350 --> 00:36:01.680
Let's get going!

627
00:36:01.680 --> 00:36:02.970
Yeah!

628
00:36:33.630 --> 00:36:36.970
Who will be welcomed by
my Ordeal of String?

629
00:36:36.970 --> 00:36:38.470
The Shandians...

630
00:36:38.470 --> 00:36:40.720
or the Blue Sea people?

631
00:36:46.020 --> 00:36:53.690
This weather is perfect
for the upcoming festival...
